{
  "texts": [
    "In fact, he gives two different constructions, depending on if J ∂ \"comes after\" I ∂ (we write J ∂ > I ∂, by which we mean that J ∂ contains the endpoint of I ∂, thinking in terms of the given orientation of ∂) or not.",
    "We will therefore need to distinguish two cases, and we will start with the one where J ∂ > I ∂.",
    "In this case, the construction in [Moc25, §3.4.2] is the following (this is a slight reformulation of p. 22 in loc. cit.",
    "in our situation and language): Let A:= Θ(⟨q⟩)̸ =0 A(q) be the set of all the distinguished sectors on all active circles.",
    "One considers the situation at the point θ 0, the endpoint of I ∂ (which is contained in the interior of J ∂)."
  ]
}